variables and a loop.

To break this down into libgccjit terms, it's usually easier to reword
the @cite{for} loop as a @cite{while} loop, giving:

@quotation

@example
int loop_test (int n)
@{
  int sum = 0;
  int i = 0;
  while (i < n)
  @{
    sum += i * i;
    i++;
  @}
  return sum;
@}
@end example

